            <title>[JDK-8310265] (process) jspawnhelper should not use argv[0]</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8310265</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Reported by &lt;a href=&apos;mailto:jarabekit@gmail.com&apos;&gt;jarabekit@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; [1]&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
jspawnhelper uses argv[0] to receive the fd string from the parent. That breaks with conventions and trips over certain tools like binfmt_misc.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
For details, see linked ML discussion.&lt;br/&gt;
